templates.text:
get("/html-dsl") {
    call.respondHtml {
        body {
            h1 { +"HTML" }
            ul {
                for (n in 1..10) {
                    li { +"$n" }
                }
            }
        }
    }
}

documentation.usage:
To send an HTML response, call the `respondHtml` method inside the required route:

```kotlin
routing {
    get("/") {
        val name = "Ktor"
        call.respondHtml(HttpStatusCode.OK) {
            head {
                title {
                    +name
                }
            }
            body {
                h1 {
                    +"Hello from         $name        !"
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
```

You can learn more from the [HTML DSL](https://ktor.io/docs/html-dsl.html) help topic.
